  <name>Valent</name>
  <summary>A KDE Connect implementation for Gtk-based desktops</summary>
  <developer_name>Andy Holmes</developer_name>

  <description>
    <p>
      Valent is a KDE Connect client for Gtk based desktops. It is written in C
      using Gtk, GLib, and other GNOME APIs.
    </p>
    <p>
      Although primarily meant for the GNOME desktop, any Gtk desktop should be
      supported and plans to support adaptable UI patterns for use on Librem5
      and other small screen FOSS devices is planned.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Sync clipboard between devices</li>
      <li>Sync notifications between devices</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

